= Demetrio Vallejo

*Corriente: los ortodoxos. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

Eleven years, four months, and some days, most of them in Lecumberri, several of them on hunger strike — he kept count of everything, it is his profession. In 1958 he led the largest strike wave since the Revolution armed with nothing but timetables and the fact that the trains do not move unless the men move them. The state has never forgiven him for demonstrating this so clearly. Small, precise, immune to flattery; he reads a wage table the way other men read a horizon.

