He goes where the CTM's writ runs thinnest — the electricians with their engineer's pride, the new industrial belts where the charro locals exist only as a dues deduction. He does not promise victories. He explains, with chalk, how a union works when it belongs to its members, and the chalk does more damage than dynamite.

@vallejo_insobornable
title: El insobornable
subtitle: The regime buys men weekly. Parade the one it couldn't.
choose-if: advisor_action_timer == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; unity += 3; political_capital += 3; fac_ortodoxos += 2; fac_renovadores -= 1; fac_nueva_izquierda -= 1

They offered him everything, at intervals, for eleven years: the plea, the pension, the seat, the silence. The offers are a matter of record; so are the refusals. When he stands next to the young cadres at a meeting, nobody needs to give the speech about the charola. He is the speech.

@vallejo_autoridad
title: La autoridad del 59
subtitle: The name itself is a lever. Spend the legend of the great railway strike on the dissident unions.
card-image: img/portraits/vallejo.jpeg
choose-if: advisor_action_timer == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; political_capital += 3; sup_workers += 2; unity += 2; charrismo -= 2; pri_reformist_rel += 1

He does not have to organize a room; he only has to enter it. The dissident electricians, the university workers, the bus drivers who have never met him know the story — the yards, the army, the nine years — and a movement that Vallejo blesses borrows a legitimacy the charros cannot buy at any price. The CTM ages another year every time his name is printed.
